              <para>In the ON position the ship's courtesy lights are
              illuminated.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/nightlights.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> NIGHT (OFF-ON)</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>In the ON position the ship's red wheelhouse night
              lighting is illuminated.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </sect3>

      <sect3>
        <title>Navigation group</title>

        <para/>

        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/wiper.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> WIPER (OFF-ON-(MODE))</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>In the ON position the windscreen wiper(s) operate. The
              operating speed and the screen wash are selected by the MODE
              position. Refer to the windscreen wiper controller manual for
              more information.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/board.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> BOARD (OFF-ON)</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>In the ON position the ship's blue board is displayed
              (moved to its vertical position); in the OFF psoition the board
              is restored to its horizontal parking position.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/horn.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> HORN (OFF-(ON))</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>In the ON position the ship's horn sounds for the duration
              the switch is operated.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </sect3>

      <sect3>
        <title>Panel control group</title>

        <para>These controls are concerned with modifying the operation of the
        helm panel itself.</para>

        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/panel.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> PANEL ((UP)-OFF-(DOWN)</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>In the UP position panel background illumination is
              increased; in the DOWN position panel illumination is
              decreased.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/silence.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> SILENCE (OFF-(SILENCE))</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>The SILENCE position cancels the audible component of any
              active alarm conditions. Note that the alarm indicator lamp will
              remain illuminated until the cause of the alarm condition is
              cleared and that any new alarm conditions will cause the audible
              alarm to sound again).</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </sect3>

      <sect3>
        <title>Safety group</title>

        <para>These controls are concerned with operation of environmental
        safety systems.</para>

        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/bilge1.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> BILGE 1 (OFF-AUTO-ON)</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>This control operates the engine compartment bilge system
              and should normally be left in the AUTO position. The bilge
              system is integrated into the ship's helm alarm system and
              operation of this control may trigger an alert.</para>

              <para>In the AUTO position the engine compartment bilge pump
              will be operated by the system float switch.</para>

              <para>In the ON position the engine compartment bilge pump will
              run continuously.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/bilge2.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> BILGE 2 (OFF-AUTO-ON)</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>This control operates the main compartment bilge system
              and should normally be left in the AUTO position. The bilge
              system is integrated into the ship's helm alarm system and
              operation of this control may trigger an alert.</para>

              <para>In the AUTO position the main compartment bilge pump will
              be operated by the system float switch.</para>

              <para>In the ON position the main compartment bilge pump will
              run continuously.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/eroom.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> E.ROOM (OFF-AUTO-ON)</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>This control operates the engine room ventilation system
              and should normally be left in the AUTO position.</para>

              <para>In the AUTO position the engine room ventilation system
              will operate when the engine room temperature exceeds the set
              point on the engine room thermostat.</para>

              <para>In the ON position the engine room ventilation system will
              run continuously.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata contentdepth="1cm"
                             fileref="resources/images/helmswitches/bcomp.png"/>
                </imageobject>
              </inlinemediaobject> B.COMP (OFF-AUTO-ON)</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>This control operates the battery compartment ventilation
              system and should normally be left in the AUTO position.</para>

              <para>In the AUTO position the battery compartment ventilation
              system will operate when the battery compartment temperature
              exceeds the set point on the battery compartment
              thermostat.</para>

              <para>In the ON position the battery compartment ventilation
              system will run continuously.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </sect3>
    </sect2>
  </sect1>
</chapter>
